.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-EXPERIMENT\-NOTE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-experiment\-note \- Append a timestamped note to a tracked run
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose experiment note [OPTIONS] <TEXT>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Append one timestamped observation to a tracked job record. Notes are append\-only and shown by `experiment show`. Defaults to the latest tracked run when no \-\-job\-id is given. Contacts no scheduler; only the tracked record (and its latest\-pointer duplicate, when it names this job) is rewritten.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fITEXT\fR
Note text to append.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to annotate; defaults to the latest tracked run.
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose experiment note 'diverged after epoch 3'
hpc\-compose experiment note 'baseline for v2 sweep' \-\-job\-id 12345
hpc\-compose experiment note 'lr too high' \-\-format json
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
hpc\-compose(1), hpc\-compose\-experiment(1), hpc\-compose\-experiment\-show(1), hpc\-compose\-experiment\-tag(1)
